Reasoning: The paper discusses the principles of consensus in communities and proposes a new form of consensus based on reputation. This topic falls under the scope of social and information computer networks, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with social networks and their analysis. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a likely category as it covers the intersection of computer science and social issues. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the paper discusses the resistance of the proposed system to social engineering and reputation manipulation. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories as the paper discusses distributed systems and multi-agent computing platforms.
